> does anybody know how to solve recurrence relations in Axiom. In Maple I =
can
> say, for example
>=20
> rsolve(a(n)+n*a(n-1)=3D0,a(n));
>=20
> to obtain
>                            n
>                        (-1)  GAMMA(n + 1) a(0)

just declare it and use it. i think you have to supply the initial
value a(0) :

(1) -> a(0) =3D=3D 1
                                                                   Type: Vo=
id
(2) -> a(n) =3D=3D - n * a(n-1)
                                                                   Type: Vo=
id
(3) -> a(5)
   Compiling function a with type Integer -> Integer
   Compiling function a as a recurrence relation.

   (3)  - 120
                                                                Type: Integ=
er
(4) ->



--=20
